nese learners of english and hungarian / rMano, Miho / Yoshinari, Yuko / Eguchi, Kiyoko -- t8. Explicit instruction on English verb structures in L2 classrooms / rKondo, Takako / Shirahata, Tomohiko -- t9. Character knowledge and reading stages of Chinese as a foreign language / rKim, Sun-A / Shin, Jeong-Ah -- t10. Developing communicative competence: The role of handover in scaffolding oral communication / rGilead, Yona -- tPart III: Practices in developing competence -- t11. Pragmatic development in the study abroad context: Impact of a cross-cultural pragmatic strategies intervention / rNguyen, Thi Thuy Minh / Le Ho, Gia Anh -- t12. Intercultural communication competence and possible L2 selves in a short-term study abroad program / rApple, Matthew T. / Aliponga, Jonathan -- t13. Corpora as an L2 writing reference tool: Classroom practice and student response / rQuinn, Cynthia -- t14. Effects of digital storytelling on japanese Efl learners: Focus on anxiety and PBL skills / rOno, Yuichi -- t15. Evaluation of two communities of inquiry / rToyoda, Etsuko / Harrison, Richard -- tIndex  aNearly half a century has passed since Hymes proposed the concept of communicative competence to describe the knowledge and skills required for the appropriate use of language in a social context. During these decades, a number of scholars have applied and refined this concept. In language education, communicative competence has been identified as a major objective of learning. This book will inform readers about communicative competence as a highly complex construct encompassing an array of sub-competencies such as linguistic skills and proficiencies, knowledge of socio-cultural and socio-pragmatic codes, and the ability to engage in textual and conversational discourse. Findings from research in related disciplines have pointed to the significance of factors that can contribute to the attainment of communicative competence. Various teaching practices and relevant Information and Communication Technology (ICT) tools will be also introduced and discussed to achieve communicative competence as a complex ability. It is a timely contribution to current research on key areas in the teaching, learning and acquisition of second/foreign languages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Aug 2018) 4aCommunicative Competence. 4aFremdsprache. 4aLanguage Teaching and Learning. 4aLehre. 4aLernen. 4aSecond/Foreign Language Acquisition.1 aBourguignon, Claire, eeditor.1 aChan, Daniel Kwang Guan, eeditor.1 aNagami, Masanori, eeditor.1 aWalker, Izumi, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishz978311060407808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018z9783110603170oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015050100 cprintz978150151428940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501505034423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501505034.jpg  a978-3-11-060407-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DSPb2018